responded: The root cause of the null dereference is in `dom_text_whole_text_read` at this line:
```c
smart_str_appends(&str, (const char *) node->content);
```
If `node->content` is `NULL`, `smart_str_appends` will call `strlen(NULL)`, causing a crash.

**Fix:**  
Add a check to ensure `node->content` is not `NULL` before calling `smart_str_appends`. If it is `NULL`, append an empty string instead.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/ext/dom/text.c
+++ b/ext/dom/text.c
@@ -78,7 +78,11 @@
 	/* concatenate all adjacent text and cdata nodes */
-	while (node && ((node->type == XML_TEXT_NODE) || (node->type == XML_CDATA_SECTION_NODE))) {
-		smart_str_appends(&str, (const char *) node->content);
-		node = node->next;
-	}
+	while (node && ((node->type == XML_TEXT_NODE) || (node->type == XML_CDATA_SECTION_NODE))) {
+		if (node->content) {
+			smart_str_appends(&str, (const char *) node->content);
+		} else {
+			smart_str_appends(&str, "");
+		}
+		node = node->next;
+	}
```

